==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Laburnum
<hw>La*bur"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small leguminous tree (<spn>Cytisus
Laburnum</spn>), native of the Alps. The plant is reputed to be
poisonous, esp. the bark and seeds. It has handsome racemes of yellow
blossoms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Scotch laburnum (<spn>Cytisus alpinus</spn>) is similar,
but has smooth leaves; purple laburnum is <spn>Cytisus
purpureus</spn>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Labyrinth</ent>⟦br⟧
